Turkey\'s Prime Minister said Tuesday Ankara was suspending all military, industrial and economic ties with Israel and warned additional measures and sanctions would be taken against Jerusalem.
 
Recep Tayyip Erdogan\'s announcement came a day after Turkey downgraded diplomatic ties with Israel ordering all senior Israeli diplomats to leave the country by Wednesday.

Erdogan also said he was considering visiting Gaza but would make a final decision after he visits Egypt later this month.
 
Defense Ministry Diplomatic-Security bureau head Amos Gilad said Turkey has a lot to lose by taking such steps.

Israel\'s Foreign Ministry said all diplomats above the rank of second secretary would leave Turkey and others would remain in their posts.
 
The latest steps taken by Turkey are in response to Israel\'s refusal to apologize for the deaths of nine Turkish activists in a raid on a Gaza flotilla boat last May. Israel expressed regret over the incident and saidit would be willing to pay into a joint fund for the victims\' families....
Turkey\'s Prime Minister said Tuesday Ankara was suspending all military, industrial and economic ties with Israel and warned additional measures and sanctions would be taken against Jerusalem.
 
Recep Tayyip Erdogan\'s announcement came a day after Turkey downgraded diplomatic ties with Israel ordering all senior Israeli diplomats to leave the country by Wednesday.

Erdogan also said he was considering visiting Gaza but would make a final decision after he visits Egypt later this month.
 
Defense Ministry Diplomatic-Security bureau head Amos Gilad said Turkey has a lot to lose by taking such steps.

Israel\'s Foreign Ministry said all diplomats above the rank of second secretary would leave Turkey and others would remain in their posts.
 
The latest steps taken by Turkey are in response to Israel\'s refusal to apologize for the deaths of nine Turkish activists in a raid on a Gaza flotilla boat last May. Israel expressed regret over the incident and saidit would be willing to pay into a joint fund for the victims\' families....
Turkey (Turkish: Türkiye), known officially as the Republic of Turkey ( Türkiye Cumhuriyeti (help·info)), is a Eurasian country located in Western Asia (mostly in the Anatolian peninsula) and in East Thrace in Southeastern Europe. Turkey is bordered by eight countries: Bulgaria to the northwest; Greece to the west; Georgia to the northeast; Armenia, Azerbaijan (the exclave of Nakhchivan) and Iran to the east; and Iraq and Syria to the southeast. The Mediterranean Sea and Cyprus are to the south; the Aegean Sea is to the west; and the Black Sea is to the north. The Sea of Marmara, the Bosphorus and the Dardanelles (which together form the Turkish Straits) demarcate the boundary between East Thrace and Anatolia; they also separate Europe and Asia.
Turkey is one of the six independent Turkic states. The vast majority of the population are Muslims. The country's official language is Turkish, whereas Kurdish and Zazaki languages are spoken by Kurds and Zazas, who constitute 18% of the population.